body.description: Ready, set, go, go with the Go! Go! Smart Wheels® 4-in-1 Zig-Zag Raceway™. Zoom down the ramps and past the battle bumper! Ramp up first words and motor skills with a talking stunt car and track set that drive development and imagination with SmartPoint® tech. Rev up the fun of speedy track play as you race for first place with the Zig-Zag Track and Battle Raceway set-ups, or focus on sweet tricks and setting speed records with the Stunt Raceway and Super Ramp. Hear phrases about feelings and cool stunts as kids drive the stunt car over three interactive SmartPoint® areas. Press the engine or windshield to fuel imagination. Start your engines! Let’s race! Collect more Go! Go! Smart Wheels® SmartPoint® cars and track sets to explore unique responses on each SmartPoint® (sold separately). Intended for ages 1.5+ years. Requires 2 AAA batteries. Batteries included for demo purposes only. New batteries recommended for regular use.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Four Track Set-Ups 1. Battle Raceway Let's race! Grab another car and send both down the Battle Raceway. They'll push past the bumper where two ramps become one for the final showdown. 2. Zig-Zag Track Place the stunt car at the top to see it jump back and forth on the way down the Zig-Zag Track. Each ramp section unlocks fun responses from start to finish. 3. Stunt Raceway Drop in on the competition with the Stunt Raceway track. Keep racers on their toes and gear up for surprising tricks until they reach the finish line. 4. Super Ramp Watch gravity do its thing as the car happily zooms down the Super Ramp. Set some speedy records as little drivers hear phrases and racing sounds.

Features Time to Race Ready, set go, go! Zoom down the ramps for speedy interactive play with this sturdy, kid-tough track set. Super Stunt Car Press the light-up windshield to learn first words, or tap on the engine to make it roar-just like a real mechanic! SmartPoint Technology Drive a Go! Go! Smart Wheels car across the three SmartPoint locations and unlock even more responses to rev up learning.
Keep the Fun Rolling Collect all the Go! Go! Smart Wheels talking cars and playsets and let imagination take the wheel! Each sold separately.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It is tricky to get together even with the instructions
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for a friend who has a toddler that loves cars. I put it together for them so it was an instant play with toy. I am not going to lie it took me looking at the directions quite a bit to figure out how to put it together. I realized in doing that it can be configured different ways so just pick one to focus on and that makes it a little easier to figure out where to put the stickers. For the price you can't beat it. He played with this for hours and was still excited days later!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Frustrating assembly and disassembly.
reviews.reviewText: The instructions were difficult to understand, mainly because it was in black and white, making it harder to see. Would recommend adding light coloring to the instruction manuals in the future. However my main concern was the assembly and disassembly. The parts of the toy that connects to the other parts to form different track sets were very difficult for me to take apart from one another. I nearly broke the connector parts because they were so stubborn to come off each other. My son enjoyed the toy at first but I presume he quickly got frustrated with it himself because of how long it would take me to transform it into another track orientation ,without trying to break the toy, to the connectors. I would highly recommend as a fantastic toy for kids my sons age, but due to the unclear instruction manual and the tough assembly and disassembly I will be referring to alternatives when recommending similar products.

reviews.reviewText: It looks great on “paper”, but, the pieces aren’t marked or labeled in any way making it difficult to assemble patiently.-unnecessarily time consuming changing the design & it isn’t sturdy. -The cars don’t properly go down the track properly when using the 3 level design. The cars, at times, crash down each level & frustrates my 3 yr old bc he has to reposition the cars. *I had high hopes for this but my son lost interest after two days because of the inconsistencies*
My nephew loved it ! Very easy to use and kids love the different options.

This is a really fun and engaging toy! You can set it up different ways. The children in my classroom had so much fun with it! Since I have this in my classroom and lots of children will be playing with it, I'm hoping will hold up to their play. I would recommend this item!

This is a must-have toy for any kids who are into cars! This is fairly straight-forward to assemble, not taking too much time. There are a few different configurations for the racetrack, which lends more usability and creativity to this. It also comes with an included car. As with other V-Tech Smart Wheels toys, there are different responses/reactions as the car goes over certain points. It also apparently integrates with other products in the line, so there's definitely room for growth.

Build quality: Acceptable. It's your run of the mill plastic, better than dollar store quality but not absolute top-tier quality plastic. The plastic does have some flex to it, but nothing concerning during use. The car works well, scanning the codes and making the appropriate sound effects. No serious concerns regarding build quality.Use: So putting this together is relatively straightforward. Everything snaps into place with one-way latches. The main body (consisting of the two blue scaffolds and the red/green endpieces) pretty much stays as one unit throughout the different setups, and it's just sliding the ramps into place in different positions. The ramps are surprisingly not interchangable; there are specific spots they go to, so I recommend putting it together once and then putting the stickers so it matches the box/instructions so it's easier to figure it out later. My one gripe is that with the zig-zag setup, the ramps have this weird protrusion at the end that is only on one side, which makes the car do weird flips as it goes down, and sometimes ends up upside down. Fortunately the remaining setups don't seem to have any problems, with my kid's personal favorite setup being the giant ramp.Overall, it's a nice toy, and the fact you can use different setups and that it comes with a fancy light-and-sound car makes it a good, albeit not excellent, value.
